{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idd3b17810-3a6f-11f1-8dc6-9561437cf370","identifier":"/us/usc/t11/s1170"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1170"},"text":"§ 1170.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Abandonment of railroad line","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idd3b17811-3a6f-11f1-8dc6-9561437cf370","identifier":"/us/usc/t11/s1170/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" The court, after notice and a hearing, may authorize the abandonment of all or a portion of a railroad line if such abandonment is—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idd3b17812-3a6f-11f1-8dc6-9561437cf370","identifier":"/us/usc/t11/s1170/a/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idd3b17813-3a6f-11f1-8dc6-9561437cf370","identifier":"/us/usc/t11/s1170/a/1/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" in the best interest of the estate; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idd3b17814-3a6f-11f1-8dc6-9561437cf370","identifier":"/us/usc/t11/s1170/a/1/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" essential to the formulation of a plan; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idd3b17815-3a6f-11f1-8dc6-9561437cf370","identifier":"/us/usc/t11/s1170/a/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" consistent with the public interest.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idd3b17816-3a6f-11f1-8dc6-9561437cf370","identifier":"/us/usc/t11/s1170/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" If, except for the pendency of the case under this chapter, such abandonment would require approval by the Board under a law of the United States, the trustee shall initiate an appropriate application for such abandonment with the Board. The court may fix a time within which the Board shall report to the court on such application.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idd3b17817-3a6f-11f1-8dc6-9561437cf370","identifier":"/us/usc/t11/s1170/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" After the court receives the report of the Board, or the expiration of the time fixed under subsection (b) of this section, whichever occurs first, the court may authorize such abandonment, after notice to the Board, the Secretary of Transportation, the trustee, any party in interest that has requested notice, any affected shipper or community, and any other entity prescribed by the court, and a hearing.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idd3b17818-3a6f-11f1-8dc6-9561437cf370","identifier":"/us/usc/t11/s1170/d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"d"},"text":"(d)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idd3b17819-3a6f-11f1-8dc6-9561437cf370","identifier":"/us/usc/t11/s1170/d/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Enforcement of an order authorizing such abandonment shall be stayed until the time for taking an appeal has expired, or, if an appeal is timely taken, until such order has become final.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idd3b1781a-3a6f-11f1-8dc6-9561437cf370","identifier":"/us/usc/t11/s1170/d/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" If an order authorizing such abandonment is appealed, the court, on request of a party in interest, may authorize suspension of service on a line or a portion of a line pending the determination of such appeal, after notice to the Board, the Secretary of Transportation, the trustee, any party in interest that has requested notice, any affected shipper or community, and any other entity prescribed by the court, and a hearing. An appellant may not obtain a stay of the enforcement of an order authorizing such suspension by the giving of a supersedeas bond or otherwise, during the pendency of such appeal.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idd3b1781b-3a6f-11f1-8dc6-9561437cf370","identifier":"/us/usc/t11/s1170/e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"e"},"text":"(e)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idd3b1781c-3a6f-11f1-8dc6-9561437cf370","identifier":"/us/usc/t11/s1170/e/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" In authorizing any abandonment of a railroad line under this section, the court shall require the rail carrier to provide a fair arrangement at least as protective of the interests of employees as that established under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t49/s11326/a"},"text":"section 11326(a) of title 49","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idd3b1781d-3a6f-11f1-8dc6-9561437cf370","identifier":"/us/usc/t11/s1170/e/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Nothing in this subsection shall be deemed to affect the priorities or timing of payment of employee protection which might have existed in the absence of this subsection.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idd3b1781e-3a6f-11f1-8dc6-9561437cf370"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/598"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–598","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1978-11-06"},"text":"Nov. 6, 1978","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/92/2643"},"text":"92 Stat. 2643","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/448/tII/s227/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–448, title II, § 227(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-10-14"},"text":"Oct. 14, 1980","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/94/1931"},"text":"94 Stat. 1931","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/353/tIII/s521"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–353, title III, § 521","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1984-07-10"},"text":"July 10, 1984","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/98/388"},"text":"98 Stat. 388","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/88/tIII/s302/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–88, title III, § 302(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1995-12-29"},"text":"Dec. 29, 1995","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/109/943"},"text":"109 Stat. 943","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/8/tXII/s1217"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–8, title XII, § 1217","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2005-04-20"},"text":"Apr. 20, 2005","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/119/195"},"text":"119 Stat. 195","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idd3b1781f-3a6f-11f1-8dc6-9561437cf370"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"idd3b17820-3a6f-11f1-8dc6-9561437cf370"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Historical and Revision Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"idd3b17821-3a6f-11f1-8dc6-9561437cf370"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"senate report no. 95–989","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsection (a) of section 1178 [enacted as section 1170] permits the court to authorize the abandonment of a railroad line if the abandonment is consistent with the public interest and either in the best interest of the estate or essential to the formulation of a plan. This avoids the normal abandonment requirements of generally applicable railroad regulatory law.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsection (b) permits some participation by the Interstate Commerce Commission in the abandonment process. The Commission’s role, however, is only advisory. The Commission will represent the public interest, while the trustee and various creditors and equity security holders will represent the interests of those who have invested money in the enterprise. The court will balance the various interests and make an appropriate decision. The subsection specifies that if, except for the pendency of the railroad reorganization case, the proposed abandonment would require Commission approval, then the trustee, with the approval of the court, must initiate an application for the abandonment with the Commission. The court may then fix a time within which the Commission must report to the court on the application.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsection (c) permits the court to act after it has received the report of the Commission or the time fixed under subsection (b) has expired, whichever occurs first. The court may then authorize the abandonment after notice and a hearing. The notice must go to the Commission, the Secretary of Transportation, the trustee, and party in interest that has requested notice, any affected shipper or community, and any other entity that the court specifies.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsection (d) stays the enforcement of an abandonment until the time for taking an appeal has expired, or if an appeal has been taken, until the order has become final. However, the court may, and after notice and a hearing, on request of a party in interest authorize termination of service on the line or a portion of the line pending the determination of the appeal. The notice required is the same as that required under subsection (c). If the court authorizes termination of service pending determination of the appeal, an appellant may not obtain a stay of the enforcement of the order authorizing termination, either by the giving of a supersedeas bond or otherwise, during the pendency of the appeal.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idd3b17822-3a6f-11f1-8dc6-9561437cf370"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idd3b17823-3a6f-11f1-8dc6-9561437cf370"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2005—Subsec. (e)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/8"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–8","children":[],"tail":" substituted “section 11326(a)” for “section 11347”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1995—Subsecs. (b), (c), (d)(2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/88"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–88","children":[],"tail":" substituted “Board” for “Commission” wherever appearing."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1984—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/353/s521/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–353, § 521(a)","children":[],"tail":", inserted “of all or a portion” after “the abandonment”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/353/s521/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–353, § 521(b)","children":[],"tail":", inserted a comma after “abandonment”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (d)(2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/353/s521/c"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–353, § 521(c)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “such abandonment” for “the abandonment of a railroad line”, and “suspension” for “termination” in two places."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1980—Subsec. (e). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/448"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–448","children":[],"tail":" added subsec. (e)."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idd3b17824-3a6f-11f1-8dc6-9561437cf370"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idd3b17825-3a6f-11f1-8dc6-9561437cf370"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 2005 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/8"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–8","children":[],"tail":" effective 180 days after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2005-04-20"},"text":"Apr. 20, 2005","children":[],"tail":", and not applicable with respect to cases commenced under this title before such effective date, except as otherwise provided, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/8/s1501"},"text":"section 1501 of Pub. L. 109–8","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t11/s101"},"text":"section 101 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idd3b17826-3a6f-11f1-8dc6-9561437cf370"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1995 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/88"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–88","children":[],"tail":" effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1996-01-01"},"text":"Jan. 1, 1996","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/88/s2"},"text":"section 2 of Pub. L. 104–88","children":[],"tail":", set out as an Effective Date note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t49/s1301"},"text":"section 1301 of Title 49","children":[],"tail":", Transportation."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idd3b17827-3a6f-11f1-8dc6-9561437cf370"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1984 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/353"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–353","children":[],"tail":" effective with respect to cases filed 90 days after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1984-07-10"},"text":"July 10, 1984","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/353/s552/a"},"text":"section 552(a) of Pub. L. 98–353","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t11/s101"},"text":"section 101 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idd3b17828-3a6f-11f1-8dc6-9561437cf370"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1980 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/448/tVII/s710"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–448, title VII, § 710","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-10-14"},"text":"Oct. 14, 1980","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/94/1966"},"text":"94 Stat. 1966","children":[],"tail":", provided that:"},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/96/448/tVII/s710"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"“(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Except as provided in subsections (b), (c), and (d) of this section, the provisions of this Act and the amendments made by this Act [see Tables for classification] shall take effect on ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-10-01"},"text":"October 1, 1980","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"“(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Section 206 of this Act [enacting former ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t49/s10712"},"text":"section 10712 of Title 49","children":[],"tail":", Transportation] shall take effect on "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1981-01-01"},"text":"January 1, 1981","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"“(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Section 218(b) of this Act [amending former ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t49/s10705"},"text":"section 10705 of Title 49","children":[],"tail":"] shall take effect on "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1983-10-01"},"text":"October 1, 1983","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"d"},"text":"“(d)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Section 701 of this Act [enacting ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t45/s1018"},"text":"section 1018 of Title 45","children":[],"tail":", Railroads, and amending sections 231f, 825, 906, 913, 914, 1002, 1005, 1007, and 1008 of Title 45] shall take effect on the date of enactment of this Act ["},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-10-14"},"text":"Oct. 14, 1980","children":[],"tail":"].”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
